<HEADLINE> Iran Denies Training Anti-Taliban Factions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Iran today rejected the
accusation that it is imparting military training and arming the
Afghan groups opposed to the Islamic Taliban militia.
</P>
<P>
Iran has constantly sought restoring of peace and stability and
formation of a broad-based government in Afghanistan, said a press
release issued by the Iranian Embassy here today.
</P>
<P>
To this end, Iran has extended full support to the U.N. peace
efforts in Afghanistan, the release said.
</P>
<P>
"The Islamic Republic of Iran, alongside the Islamic Republic
of Pakistan has suffered worst damage over the past several years
as a result of the civil war in Afghanistan and the extent of
these losses continues unabated," it added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
