<DOCNO> XIE19970903.0020 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French Stock Exchange Market Soars by 4.11 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The Paris Bourse stock exchange
market's CAC 40 index soared by 4.11 percent today, the highest in
seven years, amid rising in other European stock exchanges.
</P>
<P>
The CAC 40 index attained 2,921.15 points at the closing, after
rising by 0.88 percent at the opening of the day.
</P>
<P>
The CAC 40 index rose by 4.12 percent on August 24, 1990.
</P>
<P>
The announcement by the German Bundesbank this morning to
maintain its key interest rates unchanged sent an encouraging wave
through European stock markets in Frankfurt, Zurich and London,
whose indexes rose by 1.44 percent, 3.34 percent and 1.67 percent.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. dollar rose from one for 6.10 francs on Monday to 6.16
francs today, after the Wall Street Dow Jones index rose by 2
percent on Monday. 
</P>
