<HEADLINE> Rehabilitation Projects Launched in Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Huge work has started in
northern Mozambique to rehabilitate the rail-port system and
create a free trade zone in the Nacala Development Corridor.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here from Maputo said the corridor will bring
to three the number of such trade zones which benefit countries
of the Southern African Development Community (SADC).
</P>
<P>
The Nacala corridor is regarded as the first project of
significant magnitude to be carried out in Mozambique.
</P>
<P>
The Mozambique railway comany will rehabilitate the
Cuamba-Lichinga line in the region and will ensure a regular link
between Nacala and Malawi, the report said.
</P>
<P>
There is a great potential in areas along the Nacala corridor
in agriculture, cattle breeding, fishing, forestry and mining.
</P>
<P>
The project will cost 174 million U.S. dollars, financed by
the African Development Bank, the World Bank, the European
Investment Bank and the European Union. 
</P>
</TEXT>
