<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Passes Bill on Agricultural Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's parliament today
dissolved the Agricultural Marketing Authority (AMA), paving way
for the privatisation of the Cold Storage Company, the Cotton
Marketing Company and Dairibord Zimbabwe Limited.
</P>
<P>
Kumbirai Kangai, Minister of Lands and Agriculture, steered
the agricultural products marketing bill through the house of
assembly.
</P>
<P>
The bill which was passed without any amendments, seeks to
finance agricultural development in Zimbabwe by establishing
agricultural industry fund whose capital would come largely from
levies imposed on producers, processors and buyers of
agricultural products.
</P>
<P>
The fund may receive capital from the state and financial
assistance from other sources.
</P>
<P>
With the passing of the bill, the AMA will be dissolved and
its assets and obligations be transferred to the state. 
</P>
</TEXT>
