community to alleviate the economic hardship of the Palestinians
incurred by the closure which cost millions of dollars in economic
losses every day for the Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
It was also regarded as a gesture to the U.S. in order to build
up pressure on the Palestinian National Authority to take efforts
to fight terrorism ahead of the pending visit to the region by
U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright.
</P>
<P>
Albright will begin her maiden Mideast tour on September 9 in
an attempt to revive the Israeli-Palestinian peace process which
has been stalled since March due to Israeli construction of a
controversial Jewish settlement in the traditional Arab East
Jerusalem. 
