<HEADLINE> U.S. First Lady to Attend Diana's Funeral </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 2 (Xinhua) -- U.S. First Lady Hillary
Rodham Clinton will represent President Bill Clinton at the
funeral of Princess Diana, the White House announced today.
</P>
<P>
Mrs. Clinton has "deep respect for her (Diana) humanitarian
work," White House spokesman Joe Lockhart said. "We believe she
will be passing among the American peoples' condolences," he
added.
</P>
<P>
Lockhart said Mrs. Clinton will attend the funeral in
Westminster Abbey on Saturday, then return to the U.S. He said
there will not be an official U.S. intone because of the
unofficial nature of the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
During his presidency, Clinton has only once traveled abroad
for the funeral of a foreign dignitary. That was in November 1995
after the assassination of Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhak Rabin.
</P>
</TEXT>
