<HEADLINE> European Shares Surge on Strong Wall Street, Dollar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Major stock markets in Europe
all sustained their Monday's rally and ended sharply higher today,
boosted by a surging Wall Street, firmer dollar and key Asian
markets' rebound.
</P>
<P>
British shares on the London market climbed sharply back above
the 4,900 level, cheered by a rally on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
A slight improvement in the Far East markets after recent heavy
losses also helped sentiment in London. HSBC was a strong
performer, responding positively to signs that the Hong Kong
market had stabilized.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE 100 index finished up 82.0 points or 1.68 percent near
the day's high at 4,952.2.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, German stocks closed higher in floor trade, with
sentiment buoyed by the higher dollar. But volumes were low ahead
of the US NAPM purchasing managers' figures.
</P>
<P>
The DAX-30 index closed 57.41 points higher at 4,047.37.
</P>
<P>
Stocks on the Paris bourse also ended firmer, building on
Monday's strength, supported by firm government bonds and the
stronger dollar.
</P>
<P>
The CAC-40 index ended up 115.31 points or 4.11 percent, the
biggest percentage gain in six years, at 2,921.15. 
</P>
</TEXT>
