<HEADLINE> IDB, WorldTel Agree to Finance Telecommunication </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) today said it has reached an agreement with
WorldTel Ltd. to finance projects in enhancing information and
communications technology in Latin America and the Caribbean.
</P>
<P>
The agreement will focus on projects in poorer or rural areas
that are particularly weak in communications infrastructure. Some
studies and several actual cases have shown that such projects can
be commercially efficient, commercially driven management.
</P>
<P>
WorldTel is a telecommunications development company
established on an initiative of the International
Telecommunications Union. It is an independent, private
organization created in London and Geneva with the prime objective
of structuring and funding telecommunications projects in emerging
markets.
</P>
<P>
IDB participation in the agreement with WorldTel is part of the
bank's Informatics 2000 initiative, designed to explore concrete
proposals for expanding the region's information infrastructure.
</P>
</TEXT>
