<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Angola Builds War Orphans' Village </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, September 2 (Xinhua) -- To settle the orphans
rendered by the 20-year long civil war, the Angolan government is
to build its war orphans' village in the central part of the
country.
</P>
<P>
The village is to be built in Kunje district, about seven km
north of Kuito, the capital city of Bie Province in the central
plateau, the village planners said today.
</P>
<P>
The Angolan government and the locals and some foreign donors
are pooling about three million U.S. Dollars are to be invested
on the orphans' village, which are designed to house about 500
children.
</P>
<P>
Kindergarten, residential houses, schools, hospitals, and
service facilities will be built in the village, according to the
village planners.
</P>
<P>
The idea to build the village was initiated by the Bie
Province locals in 1993, aiming to memorize those who have
contributed in avoiding blood-shedding, especially in Kuito and
Kunje. 
</P>
</TEXT>
