<HEADLINE> One Killed, 51 Injured in Blasts in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 3 (Xinhua) -- One person was killed and 51
others were injured today in two hand grenade attacks in the
Philippines, police said.
</P>
<P>
As several policemen were parking their motorcycles in front of
a restaurant in Manila in the evening, a hand grenade was thrown
at them and exploded.
</P>
<P>
The policemen escaped unhurt, but one person was killed and 41
others standing nearby were injured.
</P>
<P>
Police did not say whether the attacker was arrested or not.
</P>
<P>
Minutes later, another hand grenade planted on a bus bound for
Malolos, Bulacan province, blew up, seriously wounding 10
passengers.
</P>
<P>
All the wounded have been sent to nearby hospitals. Police said
the two incidents were under investigation.  
</P>
