part of her agenda may contradict with his.
</P>
<P>
However, the minister did not elaborate on the problems that
may possibly arise during Albright's maiden trip to the region,
which will take her to Israel, the Palestinian self-rule areas,
Jordan, Syria, Egypt, Saudi Arabia and possibly Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Albright's trip to the region is aimed at reviving the
Israeli-Palestinian peace negotiations which have been stalled
since Israel began the construction of the controversial Jewish
settlements in Arab East Jerusalem in March.
</P>
<P>
Tuesday, Majali expressed the hope that the U.S. secretary
will urge all the parties concerned in the region to overcome the
obstacles facing the peace process.
</P>
<P>
To make preparations for Albright's trip, U.S. peace envoy
Dennis Ross visited the region in August and brought about
security meetings between the Palestinians and Israelis following
the double suicide bombings in West Jerusalem which killed 17
people and wounded 170 others. 
