<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The baht plunged to an
all-time low today on the local market and selling prices at some
leading commercial banks on spot trading once exceeded 37 baht
against the U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
The selling price at Bangkok Bank today once hit 37.56 against
the dollar, while the baht was at one point sold at 37.65 to the
dollar at Krung Thai Bank.
</P>
<P>
