<HEADLINE> Alcohol Blast on Bus Kills 15 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 3 (Xinhua) -- At least 15 people were killed
and 12 others injured when an alcohol-fuelled exolosion blew up
their bus in the state of Samarkand in Uzbekistan Friday.
</P>
<P>
Interfax News Agency reported today that the bus was driving
from the city of Termez in Uzbekistan to Alma Ata, capital of
Kazakhstan, when the accident occurred.
</P>
<P>
A passenger, who carried 100 plastic bottles of alcohol with
him, spilled one of the bottles and tobacco from another passenger
ignited the alcohol causing the explosion, initial investigations
showed.
</P>
<P>
The Uzbek government has set up a special committee to further
investigate the accident. 
</P>
