presented by its member Leong Che-hung at a plenary meeting held
this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, the PLC also passed on the third reading the
"Hong Kong Court of Final Appeal (Amendment) (No.2) Bill 1997,"
which was put before the legislature by the Hong Kong SAR
government on August 20.
</P>
<P>
According to a previous bill, a permanent justice, who can be
appointed as the assistant chief justice, should be a Chinese
citizen with no right of abode in any foreign country. But none of
the present permanent justices meets the requirement.
</P>
<P>
Under the new amended bill, the chief executive of the Hong
Kong SAR can appoint a senior permanent justice to the post of
assistant chief justice when the chief justice is ill or absent.
