<HEADLINE> HK University's China Career Development Award Program Successful </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The first China Career
Development Award Program of The Chinese University of Hong Kong
(CUHK) has achieved remarkable success, the university said today.
</P>
<P>
According to a press release from the CUHK, the program
attracted 171 students this summer, who found the program
interesting and instrumental in understanding contemporary China.
</P>
<P>
The program, initiated by the university's Office of Students
Affairs with the assistance from the Office of Academic Links, was
the largest in scale among tertiary institutions in Hong Kong. It
aims to broaden the experience and perspective of the students by
providing them classroom and workplace training in China's inland
areas.
</P>
<P>
According to the first part of the program, 100 students who
had completed their first year of study went to Beijing to have
four weeks of training on China's social-political and economic
system, with lectures and seminars in Beijing University, Qinghua
University and Beijing Administrative College.
</P>
<P>
And 71 other students were placed at offices of Hong Kong-based
companies, government or academic institutions in Beijing and
other cities in China's inland areas, for a six-week internship
program to acquire hands-on working experience in China.
</P>
<P>
Professor Kwok Siu-tong, University Dean of Students of The
CUHK, said the program provides an in-depth and comprehensive
exercise to enhance the students' understanding of China. It also
helps to shape one's personality, to discover one's talents and
lead to one's self-fulfillment, the professor.
</P>
<P>
The university plans to organize the program next year for more
students, the professor said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
