<HEADLINE> Prices of Steel Sheets up in South Korea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Pohang Iron and Steel Company
(POSCO), one of the biggest steel makers in the world, has decided to
raise the prices of six types of cold rolled steel sheets effective
this Saturday, September 6.
</P>
<P>
The new price rise would bring the price of general cold rolled
steel sheets to 409,000 won per ton (452 USD), from 388,000 won, up
5.4 percent, while prices of tin plated, electro-coated, and oriented
silicon steel will also rise 5.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
The prices of galvanized products and non-oriented silicon
steel will be boosted by 9 percent each and will now go for 495,000
won (547 USD) per ton and 502,000 won (555 USD) per ton, respectively.
</P>
<P>
POSCO said the boost in prices of those products have become
inevitable because their domestic prices have been much lower than
their international prices, which prompted a flood of buyers to POSCO
sales outlets when other domestic steel producers raised the prices on
steel products recently. 
</P>
</TEXT>
