<HEADLINE> Offer Price for Lufthansa to Be Issued in October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The offer price for the German
state's remaining 37.5 percent holdings in the German airline
Lufthansa will be issued on October 11-12 for the planned final
privatization phase of the company this year, the German
government said in a statement today.
</P>
<P>
The final offer price will be determined by an international
book building exercise led by Dresdner Kleinwort Benson and SBC
Warburg, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
The statement said the state's holdings totaled about 5 billion
marks (2.7 billion U.S. dollars) at current stock prices.
</P>
<P>
It said that subscription would start on September 29 and run
through October 10. German investors would receive a discount on
the offer price and priority allocation for early orders, it said
without giving further details.
</P>
<P>
Under German law, shares owned by foreigners should not exceed
50 percent of Lufthansa's total equity.
</P>
<P>
Lufthansa is the world's number four airline in passenger
volume. Last week, it reported record pre-tax profits of 397
million marks (216 million dollars) in the first half, more than
tripling that in the same period of 1996. 
