Chinese Opera Carnival, Chinese Opera Parade, seminars, lecture
demonstrations and exhibitions.
</P>
<P>
The audience will, in addition to enjoying familiar and
well-known works on favorite Cantonese and Beijing operas, take
this opportunity to experience other rarely seen operative forms
such as the Hui, Qin, Han, Jin, Ping and Wu operas, plus several
popular regional operas including the Shaoxing, Chaozhou operas
and Shanghai comedy.
</P>
<P>
A spokeswoman for the Council said that the aim of the festival
is to promote the interests and appreciation of the local audience
on various Chinese performing arts and above all, Chinese culture.
It also provides a forum for the Chinese artists to exchange ideas
and experience. 
