investment opportunities in China and better utilize their
technology.
</P>
<P>
She said the Chinese government attaches great importance to
the development of central and western parts of the country and
has issued series of policies designed to encourage foreign
investment in related areas.
</P>
<P>
She noted that China is pleased to see that Japanese business
circles have exhibited keen interest in the regions.
</P>
<P>
Central and western China covers an extensive area featuring
abundant natural and labor resources, as well as great potential
for development of agriculture and mining industry, said Wu.
</P>
<P>
She described the regions as "full of hope," and noted that
various cities there have established industrial infrastructure
and integrated industrial systems.
</P>
<P>
The minister, who also serves as president of Sino-Japanese
Investment Promotion Council, expressed her belief that Japanese
enterprises will distinguish themselves based on abundant funds,
advanced technology, vast experience and their country's
geographical and human advantages.
</P>
<P>
Informed sources note that investors from more than 170
countries and regions have participated in the highly competitive
Chinese market.
</P>
<P>
Japanese investment has grown rapidly over the past two years,
with Japan topping the list of countries and areas investing in
China.
</P>
<P>
Projects under discussion indicate that China and Japan will
expand cooperation in capital- and technology-intensive fields,
and in central and western China.
</P>
<P>
Wu stressed that the two nations should place priority on
common interests in order to ensure the smooth development of
bilateral economic relations.
</P>
<P>
Problems should be resolved through equal consultation, Wu
said, adding that any discriminatory action will damage
cooperation and infringe on the interests of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Ikeura Kisaburo, president of the Japanese-Chinese Investment
Promotion Council, said Japanese enterprises have great investment
potential in China.
</P>
<P>
However, he added that greater efforts will be required to
fully display the potential in line with China's policies on the
use of foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
The 300-odd participants in today's meeting included Chinese
officials and leaders from 48 Japanese business groups, including
Panasonic, Sanyo, Canon and Mitsubishi. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
