<DOCNO> XIE19970903.0106 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ministry Proposes Expanded Reform of Rural Industries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Agriculture
recently issued "Proposals for Expanding the Reform of Township
Enterprises" urging accelerated reform to ensure the sustained,
rapid and healthy development of rural industries.
</P>
<P>
The goal of the proposals is to further accelerate reform of
the property rights system by introducing cooperative
stock-holding and joint stock systems, as well as merger, outright
sales and bankruptcies.
</P>
<P>
The ultimate goal of reform is to establish a modern enterprise
system for township- and village-based firms, according to the
document.
</P>
<P>
However, reform must fully respect the will of farmers,
according to the document which emphasizes that various forms of
reform can be adopted, and the value of collectively-owned
properties must be safeguarded and increased.
</P>
<P>
The document also clarifies the relationship between rural
enterprises and local administrations by separating the functions
of each. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
