<DOCNO> XIE19970903.0107 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Build First Riverine Container Port </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The construction of Bangladesh's
first riverine container port will soon begin, official sources
said here today.
</P>
<P>
The acquisition of land and preparation of engineering drawing,
the initial phase of the 3.55 billion taka (about 80.68 million
U.S. dollars) project has just been completed.
</P>
<P>
The container port will be located at Pangoan on the Buriganga
River in Narayanganj District.
</P>
<P>
The Overseas Economic Cooperation Fund of Japan has provided
the project with 230 million taka (about 5.23 million dollars) to
procure land and prepare drawing for the project.
</P>
<P>
The container terminal to be built on an area of 89 acres
(about 36 hectares) is expected to handle a maximum of 160,000
containers per annum.
</P>
<P>
When the container terminal is built, ocean-going ships,
particularly those feeder ships from Singapore and Colombo, would
be able to anchor there, marking a new era in the export and
import business.
</P>
<P>
Besides, this would also reduce congestion and transportation
cost otherwise needed for carrying goods from Chittagong and
Mongla Port either by train or by truck.  
</P>
</TEXT>
