<HEADLINE> Liu Huaqing Returns From Russian Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese government
delegation led by Vice-Chairman of the Central Military Commission
Liu Huaqing returned to Beijing by special plane today following a
successful visit to Russia.
</P>
<P>
Liu also serves as a Standing Committee member of the Political
Bureau of the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
The delegation included Liu's wife Xu Hongxia; Qian Shugen,
deputy chief of the General Staff of the Chinese People's
Liberation Army (PLA); Cao Gangchuan, minister in charge of the
Commission of Science, Technology and Industry for National
Defense; Gan Ziyu, vice-minister of the State Planning Commission;
Zhu Yuli, general manager of the China Aviation Industry Corp.;
and Vice-Minister of Finance Liu Jibing.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier Jiang Chunyun, Vice-Chairman of the
Central Military Commission Zhang Wannian and Deputy Chief of the
PLA General Staff Xiong Guangkai greeted the delegation at the
airport. 
</P>
