<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Karpov and Kasparov to Play for World Title in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 3 (Xinhua) -- World chess champion Garry
Kasparov and arch-rival Anatoly Karpov will play a world title
match at Compiegne, near Paris, next month, according to the
organiser here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"Both champions have just confirmed they will take part,"
Romanian-born organiser Carol Stroe said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
Stroe said the October 21-November 25 contest would take place
at the 19th-century 780-seat Imperial Theatre in Compiegne, 80 km
northeast of Paris.
</P>
<P>
"The winner of this historic match will become the champion of
the millennium and pocket 10 million francs (1.6 million
U.S. dollars)," he said.
</P>
<P>
The loser would get five million francs (800,000
U.S. dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
