<HEADLINE> Technicians Honored for Creativity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Chinese researchers and
technicians received yet another morale booster during today's
meeting honoring their many contributions recorded during an
ongoing competition.
</P>
<P>
Researchers and technicians have introduced over 730,000
technological renovation proposals annually over the past
decade. The suggestions have generated 11.8 billion yuan (1.4
billion US dollars) in economic benefits for enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The competition, jointly sponsored by the Chinese Association
of Science and Technology, the State Economic and Trade Commission
and the State Planning Commission, was launched ten years ago.
</P>
<P>
The goal of the program is to enhance the enthusiasm and
promote the creativity of technicians to ensure progress in
science and technology. Technicians are being encouraged to
undertake more extensive technological renovations and
contribute even more to the reform and modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that one million technicians have
participated in the activity annually over the past decade. In
the future, the program will center on cultural and ethical
progress, and technological innovation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
