<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hang Seng Index Makes Biggest Single-Day Gains </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's blue chips went
through the largest day-to-day fluctuation today by rocketing
nearly 1,000 points.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index, which traces the 33 blue chips listed on
the Hong Kong Stock Exchange, shot up 978.66 points today to close
at 14,713.99. The second sharpest rise was recorded on June 20
this year, when the benchmark index soared 647.87 points in a
single day.
</P>
<P>
Today's surge of 7.13 percent from the previous session was
however not the biggest in terms of percentage gains.
</P>
<P>
Turnover reached about 34.6 billion HK dollars (4.4 billion
U.S. dollars) today, the eighth heaviest in history. The Hong Kong
bourse has created all its top 10 turnover records since August 7
this year, with the highest hitting 46 billion HK dollars (5.9
billion U.S. dollars) on August 29.
</P>
<P>
The dramatic rebound today followed yesterday's big rally of
309.68 points, after a free-fall of 2,018 points in three
consecutive working days that wiped out all the gains made this
year.
</P>
<P>
Securities analysts contributed the strong momentum in Hong
Kong to an overall rebound on global stock markets triggered by a
rise on Wall Street. They seem to maintain an optimistic view of
the stock market, which has recently been riding on a roller
coaster, as the economic fundamentals in Hong Kong remained strong
and other major determining factors, such as the U.S. interest
rates, remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Stock prices soared across the board, led by property and bank
stocks, whose sub-indices advanced by 1,401.11 and 1101.92 points
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Chinese Enterprises Index, which reflects the
performance of 34 Chinese state-owned firms listed in Hong Kong,
rebounded sharply by 17 percent, or 193 points, to cover all the
losses on the previous trading day. The Hang Seng China-Affiliated
Corporation Index, a key indicator of red chips, also bounced back
by 422.17 points to close at 3.691.77.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
