<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World's Quality-Reliability Conference Held in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The Second International
Conference on Quality and Reliability ended here today, with the
participation of more than 200 scholars and experts from 16
countries.
</P>
<P>
During the three-day meeting jointly organized by the Hong Kong
Polytechnic University, Nanjing University of Aeronautics
and Astronautics and Britain's University of Warwick, the
participants presented their latest research findings and
developments.
</P>
<P>
A source close to the meeting told reporters that a total of 77
 papers were issued at the meeting, which proceeded with big
success.
</P>
<P>
The discussions covered total quality management, quality in
the service sector, continuous process and product improvement,
quality management systems, inspection and testing as well as
measurement, statistical tools for quality control, reliability
engineering, and maintenance engineering and management.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the conference, Professor Lee Wing-bun,
co-chairman of the meeting, said: "With 'quality and reliability:
key to excellence' as the theme, the conference aims at providing
a forum for participants to share their views and experience in
quality and reliability, and further promoting global awareness of
the importance of quality and reliability in various trades in
today's society."
</P>
<P>
Building on the success of the first conference held in Hong
Kong in 1995, this year's conference was attended by scholars and
experts from China, India, Indonesia, Iran, Japan, Singapore,
South Africa, Egypt, Australia, Norway, Russia, Britain, the Czech
Republic, Germany, the United States and Canada. 
</P>
</TEXT>
