<HEADLINE> Asia's Largest Jewelry, Watch Fair Opens in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Asia's largest jewelry and
watch fair opened here today, drawing a record attendance of more
than 1,500 exhibitors from 40 counties and regions.
</P>
<P>
Covering a total exhibition area of 27,000 sq. m, the five-day
trade fair displays an assortment of gold, platinum and diamond
jewelry, rough and cut gemstones, pearls, precious metals,
minerals, timepieces, accessories and processing equipment.
</P>
<P>
According to the organizer, Miller Freeman Asia, over 30,000
jewelry and watch manufacturers, traders and collectors from 80
countries and regions are expected to visit the show.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Pavilion, the largest at the fair, consists of
513 exhibitors, including fine jewelry manufacturers, pearl and
gemstone firms.
</P>
<P>
As one of the world's leading exporters of fine jewelry, Hong
Kong exported more than 10 billion HK dollars (1.28 billion U.S.
dollars) worth of jewelry in 1996, said Leung Sik Wah, chairman of
the Hong Kong Jewelers' and Goldsmiths' Association.
</P>
<P>
He expected to see a successful business result at this year's
jewelry and watch fair. "The U.S. market is very good while the
Middle East and South American markets are moving up
satisfactorily. The Southeast Asian market is stable despite the
recent currency fluctuation," said Leung.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong is the top exporter of watches in the world in terms
of quantity, and the fourth largest exporter of precious jewelry.
</P>
</TEXT>
