<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Elderly Respected in Hangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Gong Baoxian, an old man in
the capital city of east China's Zhejiang Province, always brings
along his red senior citizen's discount card when he goes out.
</P>
<P>
"With this card, I can visit any park in Hangzhou free of
charge," he says with a satisfied air.
</P>
<P>
Similar to an identification card, it has the words "Card
Prescribing Preferential Treatment for the Elderly" on it.
</P>
<P>
"I got my card from the street residents' committee. Every
person over 70 has one," Gong said, proudly pointing to his card.
</P>
<P>
Hangzhou has issued more than 80,000 such cards, according to a
city official in charge of elderly people's affairs.
</P>
<P>
Hangzhou has about 240,000 people aged over 60 in the urban
areas, which accounts for 14.5 percent of its total population. It
is one of the few aging cities in China.
</P>
<P>
To carry forward the long-time tradition of paying special
attention to old people, the Hangzhou Municipal Government has
taken measures in the past few years to guarantee the rights of
its senior citizens.
</P>
<P>
"We enjoy special treatment when we go out," said Du Yixin, an
old man who resides in Zhaohui newly-built residential area. "To
go to West Lake I have to change buses, but it costs me only two
jiao."
</P>
<P>
The bus ticket in Hangzhou is half of one yuan, but senior
citizens need only pay one jiao (about one US cent).
</P>
<P>
In addition to the special treatment on buses, old people in
Hangzhou aren't charged for use of public toilets, registering in
hospitals, boating on West Lake, visiting Lingyin Temple, museums
and memorial halls, or receiving legal advice.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the elderly can get a discount of 50 percent in
cinemas, stadiums and theatres in daytime.
</P>
<P>
"It really pleases us that we can visit any park and scenic
spot of the like in the urban areas free of charge," Du
said. "Retired people should go out into nature to build character
and improve the body."
</P>
<P>
Du, who came to Hangzhou to live with his son, said that
because of this special treatment, he and his wife might visit a
scenic spot near West Lake every day.
</P>
<P>
Hangzhou has built an old people's park, a rarity in China,
with an investment of five million yuan (about 0.6 million US
dollars). The park has been open to the public for half a year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
