<HEADLINE> Nigerian Airlines Resume Flight to Liberia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 3 (Xinhua) -- ADC Airlines, a major Nigerian
private airlines, resumed its flight service to Liberian capital
Monrovia Saturday, four years after the flight was stopped
because of the civil war.
</P>
<P>
A statement signed by the airlines' Public Relations Manager
Utibe Ukim said the flight will be operated weekly, departing
Lagos by 8 a.m. every Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Ukim said the resumption of the flight follows the re-opening
of the Robertsville International Airport in Monrovia, which
remained closed during the war.
</P>
<P>
ADC flied its first flight into Liberia in 1993, with the
inauguration of ADC Liberia, the national carrier of Liberia, in
which it owns 48 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
