<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's Imports From Malaysia Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's imports from
Malaysia recorded a 31-percent increase in the first half of this
year to 25.3 million U.S. dollars from 19.3 million dollars a year
earlier, according to trade sources today.
</P>
<P>
However, the sources said Sri Lanka's exports to Malaysia
declined by 8 percent from 187.7 Million dollars in the first half
of 1995 to 174.2 million dollars this year.
</P>
<P>
The most notable event was the Malaysian trade exhibition held
here last May which proved a tremendous success.
</P>
<P>
In the past three years, the two countries have signed
agreements for 17 projects in investment promotion zones in Sri
Lanka, of which three are awaiting construction, eight are being
constructed and six have gone into commercial operation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
