<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue to Recover on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to
recover steadily on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits
Times Industrials Index increased by 23.94 points to close at
1820.18 today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume shrank to 250.61 million units, valued
at 533.6 million Singapore dollars (about 353.38 million U.S.
dollars). Declines again led advances by 199 to 176 while 230
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Form was the most actively traded stock as it registered a
turnover of 20.82 million units. It was followed by Hotung which
had 15.66 million shares traded. Public Bank Foreign was next with
15.45 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign led the gainers of
the day as it rose by 1.7 dollars to finish at 20.8 Singapore
dollars. Local computer sound card maker Creative 50 gained 1
dollar to end at 30.2 Singapore dollars. Elec increased by 80
cents to close at 7.5 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Roth Malaya was the biggest loser as it
declined by 3.1 dollars to end at 12.2 dollars. Malaya Banking 200
and Samanda Holdings each fell by 1 dollar to close at 9.6 and 5.5
Singapore dollars respectively. Malaya Banking was 40 cents lower
to finish at 9.4 dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
