<HEADLINE> "Cocaine Condoms Men" Arrested in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Three drug couriers were
arrested at international airport here on tuesday by police with
a total of 196 condoms filled with cocaine in their stomachs.
</P>
<P>
Local media quoted a police spokesman as saying that the three
men were identified as drug couriers when they arrived on a
flight from Sao Paulo.
</P>
<P>
Police at the airport detained the men and x-rays showed that
they had "foreign objects" in their stomachs.
</P>
<P>
The first suspect, a Nigerian, passed 56 condoms filled with
cocaine with a total street value of more than 62,000 U.S.
Dollars.
</P>
<P>
The second suspect, a citizen of Cameroun, swallowed 71
condoms filled cocaine value at 82,000 U.S. Dollars. A Ghanaian
citizen swallowed 69 condoms filled with cocaine in his stomach.
</P>
<P>
In the past two weeks alone, police have arrested five drug
couriers at the airport carrying cocaine-filled condoms in their
stomachs.
</P>
<P>
The largest number of cocaine-condoms ever found in a drug
courier's stomach at the airport was 92, police said.
</P>
<P>
The South African Narcotics Bureau have in the past two months
seized cocaine worth 1.55 million U. S. Dollars from couriers
carrying the drug in their stomachs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
