<DOCNO> XIE19970903.0151 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Moving Forward with Confidence: Tung </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Chief Executive of the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) Tung Chee Hwa said
here today Hong Kong is moving forward "very well" after the very
smooth transition.
</P>
<P>
"All the three branches of our government in Hong Kong -- the
executive, the legislature and the judiciary -- are all working
very well. We are moving forward with pride and confidence. Hong
Kong is moving forward very well," Tung told reporters after
having separate meetings with Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir
Mohamad and Deputy Prime Minister Anwar Ibrahim here.
</P>
<P>
He said he explained to the Malaysian leaders that the fact is
the transition has been "very smooth".
</P>
<P>
Referring to Hong Kong-Malaysian ties, Tung said Hong Kong had
very important trade relationship with Malaysia, which is growing
at about 25 percent per annum. "It is important relationship which
we want to strengthen," he added.
</P>
<P>
"The fact is that we also have important relationship with
ASEAN nations with trade growing at 21 percent per annum over the
last five years," he added.
</P>
<P>
Tung said Malaysia this year takes the chair of the ASEAN
nations so "it is appropriate for me to be here as the first stop
of my overseas trip and to have the opportunity to talk to the
prime minister and the deputy prime minister."
</P>
<P>
On the situation of currencies of Southeast Asian nations which
are under speculative attacks, Tung said it was something sad, but
he believed that the sky will be clear after the rain.
</P>
<P>
The HKSAR chief executive described his discussions with the
Malaysian leaders as "very useful".
</P>
<P>
Tung arrived here earlier today on a two-day visit to Malaysia,
his first overseas trip since assuming office after China resumed
the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong on July 1.  
</P>
</TEXT>
