<DOCNO> XIE19970903.0153 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Three Gorges Project Yields Savings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Previously feared rampant
spending on construction of the multi-billion Three Gorges
Hydropower Project on the Yangtze River, the largest of its kind
in China, have not transpired due to effective control over
expenditures.
</P>
<P>
In fact, four billion yuan has already been saved during first
phase construction which commenced in 1992 and is scheduled for
completion in November this year when the river is dammed for
construction of the power plant.
</P>
<P>
Only 27 billion yuan of the projected 31 billion yuan has been
allocated to date and the project, which is proceeding ahead of
schedule, is fulfilling all quality requirements.
</P>
<P>
Lu Youmei, vice-chairman of the Three Gorges Project
Construction Committee under the State Council and general manager
of the China Yangtze River Three Gorges Project Development
Corporation, offered the information during a recent interview
with Xinhua News Agency.
</P>
<P>
Lu said that state investment in the project is expected to be
90.09 billion yuan if calculated on the basis of price levels in
1993 and the figure will top 200 billion yuan when considering
inflation and interest on loans.
</P>
<P>
He noted that people have for decades questioned the ability
for control of investment, and whether or not the project will
eventually become a so-called "black-hole" for investment.
</P>
<P>
Successfully curbing expenditures has enabled the Chinese
people and both domestic and overseas investors to gain confidence
in the project, said Lu.
</P>
<P>
He attributed successful control over investments to
improvements in the country's macro-economy which has in turn
reduced inflation and bank interest and has created a sound
investment environment for the massive project.
</P>
<P>
Three billion of the total four billion yuan saved during the
first phase was the direct result of falling inflation and bank
interest, said Lu.
</P>
<P>
Market mechanism introduced to the project saved an additional
one billion yuan, according to Lu.
</P>
<P>
The Development Corporation is the legal entity responsible for
project construction, fund-raising, repayment of debt and eventual
operations and management.
</P>
<P>
The project, which has adopted international practices such as
the bidding and contracting systems, on-site supervision and
contract management systems, has comprehensive competition.
</P>
<P>
The adoption of international practices has enabled the project
to obtain the honor of having the best cost-effective engineering
teams, materials and equipment, according to Lu. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
