<HEADLINE> Harare Set to Become Freight Hub </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's national cargo
airline Affretair has entered into a strategic deal with DHL
Aviation of Belgium, which will see Harare becoming a regional
freight hub, "The Herald" daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
The deal will also boost the local horticultural industry and
throw a lifeline to Affretair, said the report.
</P>
<P>
Affretair Managing Director Godfrey Manhambara said yesterday
a memorandum of understanding was signed on Monday after two
months of detailed negotiations.
</P>
<P>
The strategic relationship between DHL Aviation, a subsidiary
of DHL Worldwide Express, will see a DC8-73 aircraft with a
maximum capacity of 45 tons operating between Harare and Europe
daily while another aircraft will be available for regional
routes.
</P>
<P>
Affretair will work closely with DHL at the Harare
International Airport to ensure the timely loading and offloading
of the aircraft to reduce delivery times as well as to deliver
the products in top quality condition and as scheduled.
</P>
<P>
DHL is one of the world leaders in international shipments
with representations in 220 countries and regions. It operates a
fleet of over 200 cargo aircraft and employs over 42,000 people.
</P>
</TEXT>
