<HEADLINE> Beijing To Host National Fashion Design Contest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The sixth national fashion
design contest for the Golden Scissors Prize, also known as the
"Sunland Cup," will hold the final round of judging on September
10 in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
More than 50 Chinese fashion and fabric designers at home or
abroad have been chosen to compete for three "Sunland Cup"
prizes. Awards go to top designs in men's suits and ladies'
dresses and fabrics.
</P>
<P>
The national Golden Scissors Prize Contest, which has been held
every two years since 1985, has become the leader of its kind in
the country for everyday clothing design.
</P>
<P>
The past five contests were all sponsored by the China National
Garment Research and Design Center and have given impetus to the
development of fashion design and the sales of Chinese garments in
domestic and overseas markets.
</P>
<P>
The sixth contest is sponsored by the China National Textile
Council and is funded by Baolihua Group Co., a listed company in
south China's Guangdong Province. 
