<P>
PHNOM PENH -- Cambodian Second Prime Minister Hun Sen
reiterated Tuesday that Prince Norodom Ranariddh must face trial,
ruling out peace talks with him proposed by King Norodom Sihanouk.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen, responding to a call from Sihanouk for peace talks
with Ranariddh, said this in a reply letter co-signed by
newly-appointed First Prime Minister Ung Huot. (Cambodia-Hun Sen)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Gerry Adams, the leader of Sinn Fein, the
political wing of the Irish Republican Army (IRA), arrived in New
York Tuesday for a five-day visit to the United States.
</P>
<P>
During the trip, Adams is expected to meet in New York and
Washington with senior U.S. officials and congressmen. It is the
first time for him to visit the country since a cease-fire was
announced in July. (U.S.-Sinn Fein Leader-Visit)
</P>
<P>
