<HEADLINE> Dalian Groundbreaking Ceremony for ROK-Funded Enterprise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, September 3 (Xinhua) -- A groundbreaking ceremony for
Hyundai Electronics (Dalian) Co., a 150 million US dollar project
funded solely by Hyundai Electronics from the Republic of Korea
(ROK), was held Tuesday in Dalian, northeast China's Liaoning
Province.
</P>
<P>
The plant will produce eight million hard disk drives in its
first operational year, according to General Manager Peter
Shinn. Plans call for production to hit 20 million units by the
year 2002.
</P>
<P>
According to Shinn, the venture is scheduled for operation
by the end of 1998.
</P>
<P>
The new venture, located in the Dalian Economic and
Technological Development Zone, will employ 5,000 people..
</P>
