<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenya Exports to Uganda Fall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Kenya's exports to Uganda
dropped by 12.5 percent from recorded 280.7 million U.S. Dollars
in 1995 to 245.5 million Dollars last year, the East African
Standard newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
However, Kenya remains the biggest exporter to its western
neighbor, accounting for 33.6 percent of Uganda's market share.
Uganda's total imports were worth 729.4 million Dollars last
year, the report quoted governmental data as saying.
</P>
<P>
Britain maintained its position as second major exporter to
Uganda, with a market share of 14.18 percent or 103.5 million
Dollars of goods.
</P>
<P>
There was a general decrease in Uganda's level of imports due
to the country's emerging industrial sector, said the report.
</P>
<P>
Kenya, like other countries, mainly exports industrial goods
to Uganda, whose own efforts to develop its industrial base in
the 1970s and the first half of 1980s were devastated by wars.
</P>
</TEXT>
