<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, September 3 (Xinhua) -- A Russian-built Tu-134
plane of Vietnam Airlines carrying 66 passengers and crew crashed
today at the Phnom Penh international airport, killing 63 people,
an airline official said.
</P>
