<HEADLINE> Southwest China Province Lures Investors from East </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Sichuan, a southwest China
province, has worked diligently to attract investment from the
country's well-developed eastern, coastal areas, mainly for
electronics, textile, food and pharmaceuticals industries.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan has issued a series of preferential policies, including
those on transports, bank loans and taxation, water-power-gas
supply and telecommunications for enterprises financed by the
eastern and coastal provinces and cities, according to the
provincial Foreign Economic and Trade Commission.
</P>
