<HEADLINE> President Jiang Zemin Supports Development of Ecology-farming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Hard work and a spirit of
determination are required in the fight to protect the
environment, today's People's Daily quoted President Jiang Zemin
as saying.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper carries the full text of Jiang's comments on an
investigation report by Vice-Premier Jiang Chunyun regarding the
drive to control soil erosion and develop ecologically-sound
agricultural programs in northern Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said he believes that the long-term efforts of different
generations to promote afforestation, to green the deserts and to
develop ecology-oriented agriculture may eventually change the
existing environment.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said he was pleased to read the investigation report and
considers the northern Shanxi's experiences in the field have been
good.
</P>
<P>
He recalled that many areas in Shaanxi province, which had been
the seat of 13 ancient dynasties including the dynasties of Zhou
(770-221 BC), Qin (221-207 BC), Han (206 BC-AD 265) and Tang
(618-907), were fertile and prosperous in the past.
</P>
<P>
War conflicts, natural disasters and random tree cutting in
modern times which caused severe desertification, are held greatly
responsible for the slowing down of the economic and cultural
development, President Jiang noted.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
