<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Symposium on Beijing-HK Cooperation to be Held in October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- New ways for economic
cooperation between Beijing and Hong Kong will be discussed at a
symposium-fair to be held from October 20-21 in the Chinese
capital.
</P>
<P>
The three topics for consultations will be: how to upgrade
Beijing's infrastructure and public housing with funds raised in
Hong Kong, one of the leading international financial centers; how
to join hands in promoting the two cities' high and new technology
sector; and how to increase cooperation in finance, trade,
information, tourism and the real estates market.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that business leaders from the two cities have
shown great interest in the meeting and cooperative projects that
will be listed there. They said it is time to push Beijing-Hong
Kong cooperations to a higher level.
</P>
<P>
Lu Yucheng, deputy mayor of Beijing, expected that agreements
will be signed on a batch of major projects concerning Beijing's
urban construction.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the municipal government show that by the end
of July, there were a total of 5,247 Hong Kong-funded businesses
in Beijing. Among the total committed investment of 17.35 billion
US dollars for these business, 10.48 billion were direct
investment from Hong Kong. 
</P>
