<HEADLINE> Development Funds for Fresh Water Lake Resort in Anhui </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Anhui Province has pledged to
allocate over 300 million yuan (36.14 million US dollars) over the
next few years to build a major tourist resort on Chaohu Lake, one
of China's five major freshwater lakes.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made according to the increasing tourists
flocking to Chaohu Lake to visit the beautiful lake islands,
scenic mountains, forests, sites of historical interest.
</P>
<P>
Anhui is home to major east China attractions such as the
Huangshan and Jiuhuashan mountains.
</P>
<P>
Chaohu Lake, located near the provincial capital of Hefei, is
an ideal destination for sightseeing, holiday resorts,
mountaineering and water sports. Over 100,000 visitors attended
this year's annual Peony Festival held between April 18-25.
</P>
<P>
The ambitious development plan will transform the lake area
into the second largest tourist resort in Anhui. The area will
feature eight major scenic sites, including the Laoshan Island
Tourist Resort, the Chaocheng-Doutang Tourist and Convalesce area,
and the Taihushan Tourist Area featuring ecology tour and
religious tours. 
</P>
