<HEADLINE> Thailand to Promote Exports of Nine Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Thailand is to step up its
promotion for exports of nine categories of products in a bid to
expand the country's overall export business.
</P>
<P>
More promotion will be added to exports of crustaceans, chewing
gum, sweets not containing cocoa, alcohol and tonic drinks,
processed food, mirrors and glass, facsimile machines, cement,
printing and paper packaging, the Commerce Ministry said on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Exports of the products totaled 28.46 billion baht (1.14
billion U.S. dollars) in value in 1996, down 0.7 percent from
1995, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
However, in the first six months of this year, shipment of
these products reached 17 billion baht (680 million dollars), up
10.4 percent from the same period of last year, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
The increase showed that there was a great potential in export
of these products due to their high value-added content, analysts
said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, local newspapers today said that the ministry is
also planning to give promotion to export miscellaneous items like
perfume sprayers, ribbons and buttons.  
