<HEADLINE> Myanmar Remains Peaceful, Stable: Military Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, September 3 (Xinhua) -- "Myanmar remains peaceful and
stable in spite of all kinds of machinations of internal and
external saboteurs to destabilize the country," said Myanmar's
Army Chief of Staff Lieutenant General Tin Oo.
</P>
<P>
Addressing military officials here Tuesday, Tin Oo, who is also
second secretary of the Myanmar State Law and Order Restoration
Council, cited attempts at sabotage to destabilize the country by
internal and external elements when peace and stability were
attained and market-oriented economy practiced in the country,
official paper The New Light of Myanmar reported today.
</P>
<P>
He said the government is implementing projects for the
development of border areas and national races, making efforts to
contribute toward non-disintegration of solidarity.
</P>
<P>
The general vowed to wipe out internal strife once and for all.
</P>
