<HEADLINE> Hun Sen: Ranariddh Must Stand Trial </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian Second Prime
Minister Hun Sen reiterated today that Prince Norodom Ranariddh
must face trial, ruling out peace talks with him proposed by King
Norodom Sihanouk.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen, responding to a call from Sihanouk for peace talks
with Ranariddh, said this in a reply letter co-signed by
newly-appointed First Prime Minister Ung Huot.
</P>
<P>
He called on all the military and political officials, who went
abroad or hid at home for security reasons, to come back for
normal political and family life. Positions are reserved for them
and they will not be punished for their past deeds, he said.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen added the offer of a blame-free return applied to all
opposition members except Ranariddh and two of his top military
officials, General Nhiek Bun Chhay and General Serey Kosal.
</P>
<P>
The fate of Prince Ranariddh and the two generals is completely
up to the decision of the court, he noted.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday Sihanouk appealed for an immediate ceasefire between
the warring parties and for informal talks between Hun Sen and
Ranariddh after returning to the northwestern town of Siem Reap
from Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen also denied a proposal for informal talks with
Ranariddh by the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN)
half a month ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
