<HEADLINE> Rios, Larsson Advance to Quarterfinals of U.S. Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Marcelo Rios of Chile
defeated two-time French Open champion Sergi Bruguera Tuesday to
advance to the quarterfinals of the U.S. Open Tennis
Championships held at Flushing, New York.
</P>
<P>
The 21-year-old Rios pounded in 11 aces and cracked 39 winners
to beat Bruguera 7-5 6-2 6-4 at the National Tennis center.
</P>
<P>
Sweden's Magnus Larsson made another berth of quarterfinals by
winning over South African Wayne Ferreira, 6-3 7-6 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Larsson will face the winner of tonight's match between former
champion Andre Agassi and 13th-seeded Australian Patrick Rafter.
</P>
<P>
Rios will meet the winner of tonight's match between
second-seeded American Michael Chang and Wimbledon finalist Cedric
Pioline of France in a tournament thrown wide open by Petr Korda's
upset of Pete Sampras. 
</P>
