<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Capital Begins Collecting Discarded Plastic Food Trays </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese capital of Beijing
began collecting discarded polystyrene-based plastic food
containers on Monday, according to today's "China Daily".
</P>
<P>
Beijing's environmental protection bureau and the city's
industrial and commercial administration issued a notice on July
1, stipulating 30 per cent of such food trays should be collected
and recycled by producers next year, according to the paper.
</P>
<P>
The municipal government will revoke the production and selling
rights of producers that don't fulfill the targets.
</P>
<P>
So far, a technical-consulting center for environmental
conservation has been set up to promote the work with more than 10
collection stations across the city, according to Xie Wenxiong,
director of the center.
</P>
<P>
Under the direction of the center, discarded plastic food trays
will be collected, cleaned and classified, and turned into
products that can be used as building materials, or used to produce
gas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
