<HEADLINE> Annual Fair Attracts 1,800 From Overseas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Eight cities are sponsoring
the international trade and economic fair that began yesterday in
Shenyang, the capital of northeast China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
Backed by China Council for the Promotion of International
Trade, the Shenyang International Trade Symposium was co-organized
by seven other cities in the central area of the province: Anshan,
Fushun, Benxi, Dandong, Yingkou, Liaoyang, and Tieling, today's
"China Daily" Reports.
</P>
<P>
The yearly fair is a magnet to more than 1,800 overseas
business people from the Republic of Korea (ROK), Japan, Malaysia,
the United States, Italy, the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region (SAR), and Taiwan Province.
</P>
<P>
Forty-seven projects selected by Shenyang dealing with
industry, urban infrastructure, real estate, agriculture,
catering, transportation, and overseas construction were expected
to be on display at the five-day trading bazaar.
</P>
<P>
If the projects are all signed at the requested value, the
listed total investment will be 360 million US dollars.  
</P>
