<HEADLINE> Argentine Police Crack Bank-Robbing Criminal Group </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Argentine police have
cracked a large criminal group which robbed banks and armored cars
for transporting money in areas around this capital city, police
announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-one suspects were arrested in the crackdown operations.
The police station in Buenos Aires mobilized over 300 policemen,
70 motor cars and helicopters, and spent seven months tracking
them down.
</P>
<P>
In 31 hunting operations last week, police seized 1.6 million
U.S. dollars in cash, 59 motorcars and 34 weapons, including
rocket launchers, automatic rifles and plenty of ammunition.
</P>
<P>
The criminal group, which was the most dangerous in recent
years, was equipped with state-of-the-art weapons and
communication facilities.
</P>
<P>
It has committed more than 20 robberies since last year,
killing six policemen and taking away with 3.7 million dollars.
</P>
