<HEADLINE> Syria Wants to Rejoin Middle East Peace Process: EU Envoy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Syria wants to rejoin the Middle
East peace process as soon as possible, said Miguel Moratinos, the
European Union (EU) envoy for the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks today after meeting with German Foreign
Minister Klaus Kinkel.
</P>
<P>
"Syria is really serious when peace is concerned and wants to
rejoin negotiations as soon as possible," said Moratinos, who came
to Bonn after a weekend meeting in Damascus with Syrian President
Hafez al-Assad.
</P>
<P>
But he declined to reveal further details of his talks, saying
only, "It is important that both sides, Israelis and Syrians, want
to use the diplomatic channel and no other channels."
</P>
<P>
On the current standstill in the Israeli-Palestinian
negotiations, Moratinos noted that there are signs for progress.
</P>
<P>
Israel has become much more satisfied than before with
Palestinians' pledges to seriously combat terrorism, he said.
</P>
<P>
Both Moratinos and Kinkel hoped that the Middle East trip by
U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright on September 9 would be
able to restart the Middle East peace process. 
</P>
