<HEADLINE> Construction of Zhejiang's Expressway Being Accelerated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Construction is being speeded
up on the Taizhou section of the expressway linking
Ningbo, Taizhou, with Wenzhou in east China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
Ten km of the section, or one eighth of the total length, will
go into operation this year.
</P>
<P>
The first-phase project of the road in Taizhou, with a length
of 40 km, will be completed by the end of next year, at a total
cost of 1.29 billion yuan (157 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The second-phase project, involving an investment of 2.15
billion yuan (260 million US dollars), will also start this year.
</P>
<P>
The Ningbo-Taizhou-Wenzhou expressway, part of the large
passage in China's coastal areas, will be operational by the year
2000. 
