<HEADLINE> Britain Pledges New Assistance to Montserrat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The British government
announced here this evening that it would grant 6.5 million pounds
(about 10.4 million U.S. dollars) in aid to help the volcano-hit
Caribbean island of Montserrat.
</P>
<P>
Britain's International Development Secretary Clare Short will
visit the island in the near future, according to a BBC television
report.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, in a joint statement issued at the end of a two-day
visit to the island by Britain's International Development Junior
Minister George Foulkes, Britain pledged to build housing and
other essential facilities in the northern safe zone of Montserrat
and to help residents who wanted to resettle elsewhere.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also announced that a sustainable development
plan would be prepared within the next six months to meet the
long-term needs of those Montserratians who decided to stay.
</P>
<P>
Montserrat's Soufriere Hills volcano became dramaticly active
from July 1995, destroying many places of the Caribbean island.
</P>
</TEXT>
